laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 15 mm and is fluid-filled with hyperemia of the wall. Surrounding fatty stranding is noted. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, and pancreas are unremarkable. The lung bases are otherwise clear. A few scattered diverticula are noted without evidence of diverticulitis, and there is no free intraperitoneal fluid or free air.
